## Key Takeaways for Families

**Start here:** If your elderly loved one has Medicare and limited income, they likely qualify for some level of MSP assistance. The income limits are higher than they appear because certain income doesn't count.[2][6]

**The biggest recent change:** Florida expanded how it counts household members for eligibility purposes, which means significantly more people now qualify, especially families with multiple members.[4]

**Apply even if uncertain:** The only way to know for certain if you qualify is to apply. Income exclusions and the new household size rules mean many people who think they're ineligible actually qualify.[2]

**Contact information:** Reach out to your local county Department of Children & Families office or visit myflfamilies.com to begin the application process. Medicare.gov also provides general information about MSPs nationwide.[6]

